Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, John Brennan, spoke with Yemeni President Abdo Rabo Mansour Hadi about the political transition in Yemen. Brennan praised President Hadi's leadership and emphasized the U.S. Government's support for the full implementation of the National Dialogue. He expressed concern about reports of former government officials causing disruptions and stressed the need for all political actors to contribute constructively to the transition process. President Hadi thanked the United States for its support and reiterated his commitment to restoring stability through a political transition. Both Brennan and President Hadi highlighted the strong partnership between the U.S. and Yemen and pledged to work together, along with other international partners, to address Yemen's security and economic challenges.